-- Hargreaves Lansdown gets new money boost, sees record assets in Q1
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Tue Oct 14, 2014 02:22AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 14 (Reuters) - UK investment platform company Hargreaves Lansdown <HRGV.L> said on Tuesday that assets under administration rose to a record 47 billion pounds in the September quarter, boosted by a near 1 billion rise in net new money.

Revenues in the quarter were 70.8 million pounds, against 70.1 million in the same quarter a year earlier, while the number of active clients using its fund-picking services rose by 10,000 to 662,000, it said in a statement. Asset and client retention ratios remained strong during the period, it added, at 92.6 percent and 92.3 percent, respectively.